newsitem.title: INDONESIA: Indonesia late rubber stable on U.S. buying.
newsitem.headline: Indonesia late rubber stable on U.S. buying.

text.p: Indonesian benchmark tyre-grade SIR20 offer prices were stable in late trading on Tuesday on the back of slow U.S. buying, dealers said.

"Demand from the U.S. remains weak. I think prices are likely to stay soft in the coming days, despite the apparent tight supply, due to expected continued weak demand," one dealer in the western Sumatran city of Padang said.

Dealers said SIR20 offer prices for October/November deliveries were at 57.00-57.50 U.S. cents/lb fob Medan and at 56.50-57.00 cents fob Palembang, Surabaya and Padang, and at 56.25-56.75 cents fob Jambi and Pontianak.
U.S. firms bought SIR20 at 56.86 cents/lb fob Padang November shipments late on Monday, but the offtakes were in small quantity, dealers said.
One RSS dealer in Medan said she was in negotiation to sell RSS1 at 183.00 cents/kg fob Medan for November deliveries and expected to secure deals later in the day.
High amoniac grade latex with 60 percent dry rubber content was last traded at 2,230 rupiah/kg against the previous 2,250 rupiah in Bandung and Tangerang due to weak demand, dealers said.
